Jenkins Maven Project Tutorial (Without Maven
Archetype)
Step 1: Install Required Software
Install the following software: 1. Java Development Kit (JDK) 2. Apache Maven 3. Jenkins 4. Git
Verify installation using:
java -version
mvn -version
git --version
Step 2: Create Maven Project Folder
Create a new project folder manually. Example folder name:
my_maven_project
Step 3: Project Structure
Create the following directory structure inside the project folder:
my_maven_project
■
■■■ pom.xml
■■■ src
 ■■■ main
 ■■■ java
 ■■■ com
 ■■■ example
 ■■■ App.java
Step 4: Create pom.xml
Create a file named pom.xml in the root folder with the following content:
<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0"
 xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
 xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0
 http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd">
 <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>
 <groupId>com.example</groupId>
 <artifactId>my_maven_project</artifactId>
 <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
 <build>
 <plugins>
 <plugin>
 <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
 <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>
 <version>3.8.1</version>
 <configuration>
 <source>1.8</source>
 <target>1.8</target>
 </configuration>
 </plugin>
 </plugins>
 </build>
 </project>
Step 5: Create Java File
Create the file App.java in the following location: src/main/java/com/example/App.java Add the
following code:
package com.example;
public class App {
 public static void main(String[] args) {
 System.out.println("Hello Maven Jenkins Project");
 }
}
Step 6: Build Maven Project Locally
Open terminal inside the project folder and run:
mvn clean package
Step 7: Build Output
If build is successful you will see:
BUILD SUCCESS
target/
 my_maven_project-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar
Step 8: Push Project to GitHub
Initialize Git repository and push the project:
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Maven Project"
git branch -M main
git remote add origin https://github.com/Ramlingams/my_maven_project.git
git push -u origin main
Step 9: Open Jenkins
Open Jenkins in your browser:
http://localhost:8080
Step 10: Configure Maven in Jenkins
Go to: Manage Jenkins → Global Tool Configuration Add Maven installation: Name: Maven3 Install
automatically: ✓
Step 11: Create Maven Project Job
In Jenkins Dashboard: Click New Item Enter Name: MVN_01 Select: Maven Project Click OK
Step 12: Configure GitHub Repository
In Source Code Management select Git and provide:
Repository URL:
https://github.com/Ramlingams/my_maven_project.git
Branch:
*/main
Step 13: Configure Maven Build
In Build section provide:
Root POM : pom.xml
Goals and options : clean package
Step 14: Run Jenkins Build
Click Build Now and open Console Output. Expected result:
BUILD SUCCESS
Step 15: Final Output
The compiled JAR file will be available in Jenkins workspace:
workspace/MVN_01/target/my_maven_project-1.0-SNAPSHOT.jar









