Summary
CI/CD Flow Explanation
CI
✔ Developer pushes Java code
✔ Jenkins builds using Maven
✔ Docker image created
CD
✔ Image pushed to DockerHub
✔ Kubernetes automatically deploys
✔ Pods running inside cluster
• Jenkins clones repo
• Maven compiles Java
• Docker creates container
• DockerHub stores image
• Kubernetes pulls image
• Pods created & scaled




Spring Boot CI/CD Pipeline (GitHub + Jenkins +
Docker + Kubernetes)

Step 1: Install Tools
Install Java 17, Maven, Docker Desktop (enable Kubernetes), Jenkins, and Git.
Step 2: Create Spring Boot Project
pom.xml (important parts)
<parent>
 <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
 <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-parent</artifactId>
 <version>3.2.5</version>
</parent>
<dependencies>
 <dependency>
 <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
 <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-web</artifactId>
 </dependency>
</dependencies>
App.java
@SpringBootApplication
public class App {
 public static void main(String[] args) {
 SpringApplication.run(App.class, args);
 }
}
HelloController.java
@RestController
public class HelloController {
 @GetMapping("/")
 public String home() { return "App Running"; }
}
Step 3: Run Locally
mvn spring-boot:run
Step 4: Docker
Dockerfile
FROM eclipse-temurin:17-jdk
WORKDIR /app
COPY target/app.jar app.jar
ENTRYPOINT ["java","-jar","app.jar"]
docker build -t springboot-app .
docker run -p 8080:8080 springboot-app
Step 5: Kubernetes
deployment.yaml
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
 name: springboot-app
spec:
 replicas: 1
 template:
 spec:
 containers:
 - name: app
 image: springboot-app
 imagePullPolicy: Never
Step 6: GitHub
git init
git add .
git commit -m "init"
git push origin main
Step 7: Jenkins Pipeline
pipeline {
 agent any
 stages {
 stage('Build') { steps { sh 'mvn clean package' } }
 stage('Docker') { steps { sh 'docker build -t app .' } }
 stage('Deploy') { steps { sh 'kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml' } }
 }
}
